    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Got it. When you say \"neat and controlled\" for women, does that imply certain textures are better than others? For example, if someone has naturally curly or coily hair, should they be looking into straightening it or other ways to manage the volume so they don't look \"distracting\" in a meeting? I'm trying to figure out how to advise employees who might find it hard to meet those specific standards.",
